figgy.title: Add / populate optional fields in oai_dc
For oai_dc response, fields should not be returned if there's no data for the field

comments.body: We'd have to override some core logic to fix this, and it's not invalid XML to leave it there. Maybe this is fine?
I don't have strong feelings about it!
Characterized and derivatives generated.

Okay first, it seems like they want at least one of "text, image, video, sound." But this isn't mime type this seems to be type for the original work, like if it's a book of words they want "Text" even though what we have is of course images of it. Maybe someone else could read the documentation and confirm this interpretation. If this is the case, though, it's a pretty big ask. We'd need to create a mapping from every possible lcsh genre value that might be in figgy? Plus whatever is used in pulfa since we have both finding aid and bibdata materials. This "type" information is not pulled from finding aid objects.


Then in addition they want a narrower term but one from their list.

For example https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/293290cc-ee72-4ce5-ab49-61a303d77776 has type "Pictorial works" but that is not on their list.

Should we send what we have anyway for this second narrower term? It doesn't seem reasonable to attempt a mapping here.

No, you're right. The broader term should be achievable for those things which come from bibdata - it's the same field that powers our type facet. For the PULFA things, I guess we just default to Text?

As for the more specific terms, those are recommended but not required for harvesting.
I started doing this and ran into an issue with Hathi export. Should we just generate those JP2s on demand?
